# source-bhgd Ghost Theme — Editing Rules

## CSS Editing — STRICT

- **NEVER** use Python scripts, `sed`, `awk`, or any bulk find-and-replace on CSS files.
- **ALWAYS** use `StrReplace` for targeted edits on known, verified sections only.
- **ALWAYS** read the relevant CSS section with the `Read` tool before making any edit.
- Custom styles live at the bottom of `assets/css/screen.css` under `/* HOME CUSTOM OVERRIDES */`. Do not touch the base theme CSS above that section.

## HBS Templates — STRICT

- **ALWAYS** read the full file before editing any `.hbs` template.
- **NEVER** rename or refactor class names across multiple files in one operation without first grepping every file that references the old name.
- When renaming a CSS class, update CSS and ALL HBS/JS references in the same change, verified by `grep` before and after.

## Git — REQUIRED

- Before making any non-trivial change, confirm the working tree is clean (`git status`).
- After a confirmed-working state, remind the user to commit.
- Never make bulk changes across more than 2 files without a git checkpoint first.

## General

- No inline styles in `.hbs` templates. All styles go in `assets/css/screen.css`.
- No JS style injection. Use CSS classes toggled by JS instead.
- `old_components/` is read-only — never reference or modify it.
- The CSS class prefix for this theme is `home-`. Never introduce `bhgd-` prefixes in new code.
